cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image set recognition and face recognition, which are both sub-fields of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a feature restructuring method that uses self-attention and sparse/collaborative learning-based representation scheme. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with video-based face recognition and person re-identification, which are both multimedia applications. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as the paper deals with similarity comparison of image sets, which is a common problem in information retrieval. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes an end-to-end trainable framework that uses both parametric and non-parametric methods, which are common in AI research.
